messages.message: Hi Team - a datapoint here from a call I just had. Associated Bank mentioned specifically that any prebuilt integrations are a massive uplift for them, and a large consideration for them as they think about a solution like ours
cc @Kaustubh (KD) would be good to understand further what type of integration they are thinking (upstream? downstream? what systems they want to integrate us with)

Upstream & Downstream. Upstream from a user submitted perspective is Blend, from a broker submitted perspective I do not know yet (likely email or portal). From a downstream perspective - the LOS is Mortgage Cadence (API enabled owned by Accenture)

Good to know! @Andrew Sherrill will reach out to gather a bit more information. Curious to understand bit more about the users (how technical are they? how much access they have? which personas have access to do what), and the set of integrations/connectors that they already use across systems. Let me set up some time.

@Kaustubh (KD) - We had done some early work for M&T and BMO on blend. Below is a page on the integrations if helpful:
https://instabase.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SALESENG/pages/1855946803/Blend+Integration
